  "Camera wizard help — name": "Camera Name Help",
  "Camera wizard help body — name": "Enter a short, recognizable name for this camera.\n\nExamples: Hotel Victoria, North Bridge Cam, Port Camera.\n\nTypical mistake: using the stream URL as the name.",
  "Camera wizard help — source": "Camera Source Help",
  "Camera wizard help body — source": "Choose the stream type that matches your camera feed.\n\nSupported: HLS (.m3u8), RTSP, MJPEG, HTTP Stream.\n\nTypical mistake: selecting HLS for a plain JPEG snapshot URL.",
  "Camera wizard help — url": "Stream URL Help",
  "Camera wizard help body — url": "Paste the full stream address from your camera or hosting provider.\n\nExamples:\nhttps://example.com/live/stream.m3u8\nrtsp://camera.example.com/stream1\n\nTypical mistake: missing http:// or https://.",
  "Camera wizard help — position": "Camera Position Help",
  "Camera wizard help body — position": "By default the camera uses your Observation Point coordinates.\n\nChoose map selection if the camera is physically somewhere else.\n\nTypical mistake: placing the camera far from its real location.",
  "Camera wizard help — heading": "Camera Direction Help",
  "Camera wizard help body — heading": "Heading is the direction the camera faces (0–359°).\n\n0° is north, 90° is east.\n\nUse the map to click a target direction or enter the value manually.",
  "Camera wizard help — fov": "Field of View Help",
  "Camera wizard help body — fov": "Field of view is the horizontal angle covered by the camera.\n\nTypical values: 60° (telephoto), 90° (standard), 120° (wide).\n\nTypical mistake: setting FOV wider than the real lens.",
  "Camera wizard help — distance": "Maximum Distance Help",
  "Camera wizard help body — distance": "Maximum view distance limits how far the camera can observe vessels.\n\nUse presets for common ranges or enter a custom value in kilometres.",
  "Camera wizard help — test": "Connection Test Help",
  "Camera wizard help body — test": "Test the stream before saving.\n\nA successful test confirms the URL is reachable.\n\nTypical mistake: saving a URL that works only on a local network without VPN.",
  "Camera wizard help — summary": "Summary Help",
  "Camera wizard help body — summary": "Review all settings before saving.\n\nThe camera will be linked to the active Observation Point.\n\nYou can edit it later from the Dashboard.",
