  "Observation Point Optimization": "Observation Point Optimization",
  "RTL-SDR observation tips — no point": "Set an observation point in Project X for location-specific advice.\n\nGeneral tips:\n• Mount the antenna outdoors as high as possible\n• Keep away from metal roofs, walls, and electrical noise\n• Aim toward open water rather than inland\n• Use quality coax and a marine VHF antenna tuned for 162 MHz AIS",
  "RTL-SDR observation tips": "Observation point: {name}\nCoordinates: {latitude}, {longitude}\n\nRecommended placement:\n• Antenna near this location with clear view toward nearby waterways\n• Higher elevation improves range over hills and buildings\n• Avoid shadowing from trees, masts, or structures between antenna and water\n• AIS is line-of-sight — small height gains often help more than amplifier gain",
  "RTL-SDR configured.": "RTL-SDR configured.",
  "Hybrid mode is now available.": "Hybrid mode is now available.",
  "What is this?": "What is this?",
  "How do I fix common problems?": "How do I fix common problems?",
  "RTL-SDR help — what is RTL-SDR": "What is RTL-SDR?",
  "RTL-SDR help body — what is RTL-SDR": "RTL-SDR is a USB software-defined radio based on the Realtek RTL2832 chip. With AIS-Catcher it decodes marine AIS transmissions on 162 MHz.\n\nWhy do I need it?\nLocal reception adds vessels near you that Internet AIS may miss, and enables Hybrid mode.",
  "RTL-SDR help — Windows problems": "Common Windows problems",
  "RTL-SDR help body — Windows problems": "• Driver: use Zadig to install WinUSB on the RTL2832 interface.\n• Device busy: close SDR# and other RTL apps.\n• No device: try another USB port; avoid unpowered hubs.\n• AIS-Catcher: confirm the executable path and that port 10110 is free.\n• Firewall: allow AIS-Catcher if Windows blocks it.",
  "RTL-SDR help — Linux problems": "Common Linux problems",
  "RTL-SDR help body — Linux problems": "• Permission denied: add udev rules and replug the device.\n• Kernel driver conflict: blacklist dvb_usb_rtl28xxu.\n• rtl_test not found: install the rtl-sdr package.\n• AIS-Catcher: verify the binary is executable and listening on port 10110.\n• No messages: check antenna, gain, and line of sight to water.",
